What is the primary function of the ROLLBACK command?
A) Save the changes made by a transaction
B) Undo the changes made by a transaction 
C) Delete the table structure

(Answer: B)

What will happen if you try to insert a duplicate value into a column with a UNIQUE constraint?
A) Data will be inserted
B) SQL will ignore the duplicate value
C) SQL will throw an error

(Answer: C)

Which keyword is used to specify the join condition in SQL?
A) WHERE
B) ON
C) USING

(Answer: B)

What is the primary purpose of a primary key in SQL?
A) Ensure data redundancy
B) Uniquely identify each record
C) Establish a connection between tables

(Answer: B)

Which of the following statements is true about a Unique Key?
A) It allows duplicate values in a column
B) It uniquely identifies each record in a table
C) It is used for table relationships

(Answer: B)

In which join are all records from the left table and matching records from the right table returned?
A) RIGHT JOIN
B) FULL JOIN
C) LEFT JOIN

(Answer: c)

Which language category does the SELECT statement belong to?
A) DML
B) DQL
C) DCL

(Answer: B)

Which of the following is a Transaction Control Language (TCL) command?
A) COMMIT
B) SELECT
C) DROP

(Answer: A)

What happens when there is no match in a FULL JOIN?
A) It returns NULL for unmatched columns
B) It throws an error
C) It returns only the matched rows

(Answer: A)

Which type of join returns all records from the right table and matching records from the left table?
A) INNER JOIN
B) RIGHT JOIN
C) FULL JOIN

(Answer: B)

Can a table have multiple primary keys?
A) Yes
B) No
C) Only in special cases

(Answer: B)

Which SQL command is used to update records in a table?
A) UPDATE
B) MODIFY
C) ALTER

(Answer: A)

Which SQL join returns all records from both tables, with NULLs for unmatched records?
A) INNER JOIN
B) FULL JOIN
C) LEFT JOIN

(Answer: B)

Which SQL statement is used to delete a table completely?
A) DROP
B) DELETE
C) TRUNCATE

(Answer: A)

Which key is used to establish a relationship between two tables?
A) Primary Key
B) Foreign Key
C) Unique Key

(Answer: B)
